post_text:
😷 MASKS and NECK BUFFS😷

The masks and neck buffs below have been ordered and will be available to purchase. When they arrive, we will inform you of how to place your order. The masks will have an overhead string that can be adjusted as seen in the example below.

Neck Buffs- $10
Masks - $8

According the Superintendent’s town hall zoom meeting and the Louisiana Department of Education, all students in grades 3-12 must have a mask/face covering while attending school face-to-face. Students may wear their own masks or neck buffs (no bandanas), as long as there is no profanity or inappropriate language or images, no political statements and no confrontational subject matter.

We are currently working on a document to add to our student handbook that will list all of the COVID-19 requirements.

Thank you for your continued support as we navigate through these different times and have the safety of your children as our main priority.

Louisiana 4-H
May 28 at 10:00 AM ·

Alright STOP! Collaborate and LISTEN! Camp is BACK in a brand new FORMAT! Yes! You read that correctly!

2 months of VIRTUAL SUMMER CAMP with Grant Walker Educational Center is starting June 8. 4 tracks will be offered over the next two months including: SET (Science, Engineering & Technology), Growth in Gardening, Shoot for the Stars (Photography and Videography), and BBQ Bootcamp (Animal/Meat Science). Lessons are primarily designed for 4-6 graders; however, there will be some lessons that are suitable for 2nd grade all the way to 8th.

Register TODAY: https://bit.ly/LA4-HCamp

P.S. Camp registration is open to ALL youth this year--whether enrolled in 4-H or not and is being offered at ZERO cost, so feel free to share and get the word out!

For questions or concerns, please reach out to Grant Walker's Educational Programs Coordinator, Adam O'Malley via email at AOMalley@agcenter.lsu.edu

See y'all around the campfire real soon! #InspireKidsToDo #Louisiana4H #CloversOnTheBayou #GrantWalkerEducationalCenter #VirtualSummerCamp

Seniors and Senior parents:

Although we are unable to continue meeting with students in person, Career Compass is committed to our goal of helping graduating seniors make a realistic post-secondary plan, as well as help them in FAFSA completion. We have begun reaching out to students via email, text and phone calls to continue our work with the students. We are also trying to see which ones need some additional help with the FAFSA application. The following link allows us to gather contact information from those who would like to take advantage of the access to our FAFSA coaches. Please click the link below to complete a form to receive contact from a Career Compass representative to help complete your FAFSA

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfDYL1Lk8ROzxYbvqyt8rncbuSDilG0SU_SIexb2vRIyE0mfg/viewform

Congratulations to Mr. Chris Hightower (High School) and Mr. Chris Scroggs (Junior High). These two Summerfield teachers were selected as Claiborne Parish’s, 2018-19 Teacher of the Year. They were recognized and honored at tonight’s School Board meeting.

And I we don’t want to forget and congratulate Ms. Julia Rockett (Elementary). She was our school selection for 2018-19 Teacher of the Year!

We are so proud of them and their efforts with all of the Summerfield students and community.
